msgid "How do I force IPv4 or IPv6?"
msgstr "How do I force IPv4 or IPv6?"

msgid "Use <code>curl -4</code> or <code>curl -6</code> to specifically check your IPv4 or IPv6 address."
msgstr "Use <code>curl -4</code> or <code>curl -6</code> to specifically check your IPv4 or IPv6 address."

msgid "How do I get a JSON response?"
msgstr "How do I get a JSON response?"

msgid "Send a request to the <code>/json</code> endpoint, or send a request with the <code>application/json</code> header."
msgstr "Send a request to the <code>/json</code> endpoint, or send a request with the <code>application/json</code> header."

msgid "Can I call your service programmatically?"
msgstr "Can I call your service programmatically?"

msgid "Sure, but please respect our rate limits. Normally it's 30 RPM, and under heavy load we may drop it to 10 or 5 RPM."
msgstr "Sure, but please respect our rate limits. Normally it's 30 RPM, and under heavy load we may drop it to 10 or 5 RPM."

msgid "The API is meant for manual use or small projects. If your site uses our API to look up visitor IPs, please use a message queue so requests don't block. If your project has high traffic or needs low latency, you're better off using our open source offline database: <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/Merged-IP-Data\">Merged IP Database</a>. That's actually what this project uses under the hood."
msgstr "The API is meant for manual use or small projects. If your site uses our API to look up visitor IPs, please use a message queue so requests don't block. If your project has high traffic or needs low latency, you're better off using our open source offline database: <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/Merged-IP-Data\">Merged IP Database</a>. That's actually what this project uses under the hood."

msgid "Where does the IP data come from?"
msgstr "Where does the IP data come from?"

msgid "Geolocation data mainly comes from the free databases by Maxmind and DB-IP. AS data comes from IPinfo's free database. Proxy data comes from my own <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/OpenProxyDB\">OpenProxyDB</a>."
msgstr "Geolocation data mainly comes from the free databases by Maxmind and DB-IP. AS data comes from IPinfo's free database. Proxy data comes from my own <a href=\"https://github.com/NetworkCats/OpenProxyDB\">OpenProxyDB</a>."

msgid "Data attributions:"
msgstr "Data attributions:"

msgid "Can I run my own instance?"
msgstr "Can I run my own instance?"

msgid "Yes, the source code and database are both open source and on GitHub:"
msgstr "Yes, the source code and database are both open source and on GitHub:"

msgid "How is this website different from other IP lookup sites?"
msgstr "How is this website different from other IP lookup sites?"

msgid "The biggest thing is proxy detection. Our database covers proxy related data and the accuracy is really good. We've tested it privately against commercial databases like IPinfo's, and we hold up just as well, and actually do better on residential proxy detection."
msgstr "The biggest thing is proxy detection. Our database covers proxy related data and the accuracy is really good. We've tested it privately against commercial databases like IPinfo's, and we hold up just as well, and actually do better on residential proxy detection."

msgid "We also have better IPv6 geolocation coverage since we merge multiple databases together, so the data ends up being more complete."
msgstr "We also have better IPv6 geolocation coverage since we merge multiple databases together, so the data ends up being more complete."

msgid "The UX is also better than most IP lookup sites out there. The site runs without any JavaScript, and we only pull in a minimal amount of external resources (fonts and icons), so it loads fast on the first visit."
msgstr "The UX is also better than most IP lookup sites out there. The site runs without any JavaScript, and we only pull in a minimal amount of external resources (fonts and icons), so it loads fast on the first visit."

msgid "Is this service reliable?"
msgstr "Is this service reliable?"

msgid "The whole thing is written in Rust, so performance is great. It can handle L7 DDoS traffic and stay up fine. It runs on a 2 core 2 GB VPS, which is already more than enough. The only thing that could cause real trouble is a large scale L7 DDoS, but we have Cloudflare in front of us."
msgstr "The whole thing is written in Rust, so performance is great. It can handle L7 DDoS traffic and stay up fine. It runs on a 2 core 2 GB VPS, which is already more than enough. The only thing that could cause real trouble is a large scale L7 DDoS, but we have Cloudflare in front of us."

msgid "It costs me $18.00/month to run, which is pretty cheap. I'm not going to shut it down over hosting costs anytime soon, and there won't be any ads."
msgstr "It costs me $18.00/month to run, which is pretty cheap. I'm not going to shut it down over hosting costs anytime soon, and there won't be any ads."

